ATTENDEE;CUTYPE=INDIVIDUAL;ROLE=REQ-PARTICIPANT;PARTSTAT=ACCEPTED;CN=godau.
 j@gmail.com;X-NUM-GUESTS=0:mailto:godau.j@gmail.com
ATTENDEE;CUTYPE=INDIVIDUAL;ROLE=REQ-PARTICIPANT;PARTSTAT=ACCEPTED;CN=zufar.
 sunagatov@gmail.com;X-NUM-GUESTS=0:mailto:zufar.sunagatov@gmail.com
X-GOOGLE-CONFERENCE:https://meet.google.com/nnw-kgaq-toz
CREATED:20210827T191347Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Name: The Mentoring Club - Session with J. Godau\n\nHi!\n
 \nThanks for subscribing for a mentoring session with me. We are excited to
  get to know you and work with you on your current challenge.\n\n \n\nWhat'
 s next?\n\nPlease select the date and time that works best for you. Once yo
 u’ve selected your slot you'll receive an invite with a Google Hangout link
 . Once the session started and we are both in\, we will briefly introduce o
 urselves and then jump right into whatever you have in mind. Hopefully you 
 can take as much as possible out of this session.\n\n \n\nLooking forward t
 o meet you\n\nJack Godau\n\n\n\nHallo\n\nfreut mich\, dass du eine Mentorin
 g-Session mit mir buchen möchtest. Ich freue mich dich kennenzulernen und m
 it dir an deinen Herausforderungen zu arbeiten.\n\n \n\nWie geht es weiter?
 \n\nWähle ein Datum und Zeit die dir passt. Im anschluss erhälst du dann ei
 nen Google Hangouts-Link.\n\nWenn die Session beginnt\, werden wir uns kurz
  gegenseitig vorstellen und dann direkt in deine Themen einsteigen. Hoffent
 lich können wir dir dann gemeinsam weiterhelfen.\n\n \n\nIch freue mich dic
 h kennenzulernen.\n\nJörg Godau\n\nLocation: This is a Google Meet web conf
 erence.\nYou can join this meeting from your computer\, tablet\, or smartph
 one.\nhttps://calendly.com/events/DIGB5O2T6J6HEEKS/google_meet\n\nPlease sh
 are anything that will help us to have a great conversation: Specify your c
 hallenge\, list questions etc. Bitte teile mir alles mit\, was uns helfen w
 ird deine Fragen zu beantworten. Vor welcher Herausforderung stehst du? Wel
 che Fragen hast du? :\nHello! My name is Zufar.\nNice to meet you here.\nI 
 am a java/kotlin backend developer from Moscow\, Russia.\nhttps://www.linke
 din.com/in/zufar-sunagatov/\n\nMy current desire is to move to Germany and 
 improve my IT knowledge.\n\nIf it is possible\, I would like to ask you to 
 help me. May be you can recommend something and help me.\n1) how I can lear
 n AWS\, Docker\, Kubernetes\, CI/CD. I want to understand how to work with 
 them\, because a lot of job positions require these technologies.\n2) how I
  can solve algorithm tasks in Leetcode\, Algoexpert effectively to pass an 
 interview in FAANG in the future.\n3) how I can improve my knowledge of Jav
 a\, Kotlin\, Sring Boot framework\, Postgres database\, SQL to develop mode
 rn applications.\n4) how I can improve my understanding of Microservice arc
 hitecture. I want to know how to develop perfect architecture.\n5) how I ca
 n improve my CV and LinkedIn profile to be interesting for recruters and IT
  companies.\n6) how I can improve my career path. I can imagine that it is 
 good idea to move to the USA because there are a lot of interesting compani
 es\, projects\, people and so on. I would like to discuss it.\n7) how I can
  relocate to Europe or The USA. May be I use LinkedIn and speak with recrut
 ers in wrong way. I would like to discuss it either.\n\nIf we can discuss o
 ne of these questions\, write me please\, I will prepare questions for this
  topic.\n\nBest Regards\nZufar Sunagatov\n\nReschedule Reason: Hello J. God
 au\,\nI hope everything is okay with you.\nI'm afraid I won't be able to me
 et with you today because I'm a little sick.\nMay I reschedule my appointme
 nt to another day?\n\nBest Regards\,\nZufar Sunagatov\n\nNeed to make chang
 es to this event?\nCancel: https://calendly.com/cancellations/AME2XA5LGFH6Y
 6GC\nReschedule: https://calendly.com/reschedulings/AME2XA5LGFH6Y6GC\n\nPow
 ered by Calendly.com\n\n\n-::~:~::~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~
 :~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~::~:~::-\nJoin with Google Meet: https://meet
 .google.com/nnw-kgaq-toz\n\nLearn more about Meet at: https://support.googl
 e.com/a/users/answer/9282720\n\nPlease do not edit this section.\n-::~:~::~
 :~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~::~:~
 ::-
LAST-MODIFIED:20230106T091428Z
LOCATION:Google Meet (instructions in description)
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Zufar and J. Godau
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
