 ;</p><ul><li><ol><li>Visual comparison of data-heavy EMR screen (<strong>Pa
 tient Chart View</strong>) example from both Carbon and Lightning - Ciaran<
 /li><li>Compare key points of using Carbon vs Lightnight with style guide v
 s design system approach - Brandon\, Romain\, Ciaran</li></ol></li><li><u>W
 hat people can do right away:</u><ul><li><strong>See and share the video tu
 torial&nbsp\;<em>Using CSS from Third Party Style Guides.&nbsp\;</em></stro
 ng>This is an example of how we might easily pull from style guide into our
  own system via dev tools &amp\; copying CSS.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<a href="https:/
 /www.youtube.com/watch?v=LeCJvXwMYD0&feature=emb_logo">https://www.youtube.
 com/watch?v=LeCJvXwMYD0&amp\;feature=emb_logo</a></li><li><strong>Look at L
 ightning &amp\; Carbon component blueprints</strong>&nbsp\;- this is where 
 newer devs would pull from to contribute more\, faster. Please have a look—
 these are a way of making it easy to build styled components without introd
 ucing hard-to-manage dependencies into the application.&nbsp\;<a href="http
 s://www.lightningdesignsystem.com/components/overview/">https://www.lightni
 ngdesignsystem.com/components/overview/</a></li></ul></li></ul><p><span>8:3
