 ing-21799</a><br><br><br><br><h5><b>Project description</b></h5><p>10am-7pm
  EST hours<br>This is a unique opportunity to get in on the ground floor of
  a greenfield development project to design and develop a low-latency\, ele
 ctronic trading platform for interest rate swaps\, US treasuries and future
 s. In this role\, you will interact directly with trading\, quantitative\, 
 compliance and risk\, and IT functions to deliver new trading capabilities 
 and services leveraging modern technologies and data &amp\; software archit
 ectures.<br>For Hybrid Remote work salaries from 130000-190000 USD per year
  dependent on knowledge and skill<br>For other locations as dependent on lo
 cation and market standards</p><br><h5><b>Responsibilities</b></h5><br><br>
 bullet icon<p>Hands on Senior Java Developer with over 5 years of enterpris
 e development experience</p><br>bullet icon<p>Work with multiple business t
 eams including trading and quantitative analysts</p><br>bullet icon<p>Provi
 de work estimates as needed</p><br>bullet icon<p>Develop system architectur
 es\, designs and concepts</p><br>bullet icon<p>Maintain and improve code qu
 ality using static &amp\; dynamic code analyses\, security vulnerability sc
 ans\, code coverage and CI/CD pipeline gating</p><br>bullet icon<p>Provide 
 technical guidance and be a technical mentor to the development team</p><br
 >bullet icon<p>Design\, build and configure applications to meet business p
 rocess and application requirements</p><br>bullet icon<p>Participate in all
  phases of software delivery lifecycle from analysis through support.</p><b
 r><h5><b>Skills</b></h5><p>Must have</p><br><br>bullet icon<p>5+ years of c
 ore Java server development experience with a focus on electronic trading s
 ystems.</p><br>bullet icon<p>Experienced Java Developer (JDK 11 or 17)</p><
 br>bullet icon<p>Experience designing and supporting low latency\, high thr
 oughput trading applications</p><br>bullet icon<p>Spring (including Spring 
 Boot and Spring Boot Actuator)</p><br>bullet icon<p>Apache Camel (Version 3
 )</p><br>bullet icon<p>REST API (including Enterprise Authentication and Au
 thentication)</p><br>bullet icon<p>Enterprise services (including monitorin
 g\, state management)</p><br>bullet icon<p>JMS (Active MQ or similar)</p><b
 r>bullet icon<p>MS SQL Server and/or Sybase experience</p><br>bullet icon<p
 >Extensive experience with asynchronous\, event-driven programming &amp\; c
 oncurrency</p><br>bullet icon<p>Working knowledge of Agile\, CI/CD tools (J
 enkins\, Git\, SonarQube)</p><br>bullet icon<p>Proven track record of leadi
 ng small-to-medium teams\, mentoring developers\, and managing deliverables
 </p><br>bullet icon<p>Excellent communication and stakeholder management.</
 p><br>bullet icon<p>Strong problem-solving and analytical skills.</p><br>bu
 llet icon<p>Ability to handle multiple priorities in a fast-paced environme
 nt.</p><br>bullet icon<p>Proactive\, self-motivated\, and team oriented.</p
 ><br>bullet icon<p>Bachelor degree in Mathematics\, Engineering or Computer
  Science.</p><p>Nice to have</p><br><br>bullet icon<p>Experience designing\
 , developing and maintaining low-latency electronic trading solutions for U
 S treasuries\, futures or swaps.</p><br>bullet icon<p>Experience integratin
 g proprietary components with ION\, TradeWeb or Bloomberg</p><br>bullet ico
 n<p>Experience with Capital Markets\, understanding how Derivatives instrum
 ents are priced and valued\, RFQ workflow</p><br><h5><b>Other</b></h5><br><
