 <p><b><i>General info:</i></b></p><p><i>The Software Architect is responsib
 le for defining and maintaining the architecture</i></p><p><i>vision\, stan
 dards\, and patterns across the Software Engineering landscape. The role</i
 ></p><p><i>works closely with the Head of Software Engineering\, Test Manag
 er\, Development</i></p><p><i>Manager\, and the Architecture team to ensure
  consistency\, quality\, and alignment with</i></p><p><i>business and techn
 ical objectives across all development squads. The Software Architect</i></
 p><p><i>provides technical leadership\, and guidance to development squads 
 to ensure</i></p><p><i>architectural decisions enable performance\, scalabi
 lity\, security\, resilience\, and</i></p><p><i>maintainability.</i></p><p>
 <b><i>Experience\, Knowledge\, Personal Specification &amp\; Qualifications
  Required:</i></b></p><p>• Extensive experience in software architecture an
 d design\, with a strong</p><p>background across multiple languages and fra
 meworks</p><p>• Excellent understanding of architectural patterns\, princip
 les and best practices</p><p>• Experience with cloud platforms\, DevOps and
  CI/CD pipelines</p><p>• Experience of API design\, event driven\, and micr
 oservice architectures</p><p>• Strong knowledge of scalability\, performanc
 e\, resilience\, and security best</p><p>practices</p><p>• Educated to degr
 ee level in Computer Science or equivalent\, or has demonstrated</p><p>simi
 lar capabilities by experience</p><p>• Excellent communication and interper
 sonal skills\, with the ability to explain</p><p>complex technical concepts
  to non-technical stakeholders</p><p>• Strong analytical and problem solvin
 g skills</p><p>• Experience working in Agile environments\, specifically Sc
 rum and Kanban</p><p>• Ability to work effectively as part of a cross-funct
 ional team</p><p>• Familiar with enterprise architecture frameworks and met
 hodologies<b><i>Experience\, Knowledge\, personal specification &amp\; Qual
 ifications Desirable:</i></b></p><p>• Previous work experience of transport
  sector or similar would be an advantage</p><p>• Experience with large scal
 e distributed systems\, ideally using microservice and</p><p>event driven a
 rchitectures</p><p>• Experience of performance optimisation and scalability
 </p><p>• Experience with containerisation and orchestration technologies</p
 ><p><b><i>Responsibilities:</i></b></p><p>• Define and maintain architectur
 al standards\, patterns\, and best practices for the</p><p>Software Enginee
 ring capability</p><p>• Work with the Software Engineering leadership to de
 velop\, maintain\, and support</p><p>the delivery of the technical strategy
  and roadmap</p><p>• Collaborate with the development leads to ensure consi
 stency across squads</p><p>• Review and approve major architectural decisio
 ns and changes across the</p><p>development squads</p><p>• Work with the Ar
 chitecture team to ensure alignment with solution\, domain\, and</p><p>ente
