DESCRIPTION:Hi Zufar\,\n\nPlease find the details below for your interview 
 with American Express! Amelia will give you a call before your interview to
  help you prepare and answer any questions you may have.\n\nPlease reply-al
 l “CONFIRMED” when you have reviewed this email!\n\nInterview Details:\n\n 
  *   Date: Friday 4th July 2025 @ 12:00pm BST\n  *   Interview: Webex\n  * 
   Interviewer: Matthew Potts (https://www.linkedin.com/in/matthew-potts-292
 4a511/)\n\nInterview Link:\n~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-\n-
 - Do not delete or change any of the following text. --\n\nWhen it's time\,
  join your Webex meeting here.\n\n\nJoin meeting<https://ig.webex.com/ig/j.
 php?MTID=m90098e6123c74e848c134f1b07db2db9>\n\nMore ways to join:\n\nJoin f
 rom the meeting link\nhttps://ig.webex.com/ig/j.php?MTID=m90098e6123c74e848
 c134f1b07db2db9\n\n\nJoin by meeting number\nMeeting number (access code): 
 2432 846 6892\nMeeting password: snStfvCN932\n\nTap to join from a mobile d
 evice (attendees only)\n+1-415-655-0001\,\,24328466892##<tel:%2B1-415-655-0
 001\,\,*01*24328466892%23%23*01*> US Toll\n+1-647-484-1598\,\,24328466892##
 <tel:%2B1-647-484-1598\,\,*01*24328466892%23%23*01*> Canada Toll (Toronto)\
 n\nJoin by phone\n+1-415-655-0001 US Toll\n+1-647-484-1598 Canada Toll (Tor
 onto)\nGlobal call-in numbers<https://ig.webex.com/ig/globalcallin.php?MTID
 =m880b3054cd83ed1934c96a9ea54743a7>  |  Toll-free calling restrictions<http
 s://cisco.com/go/tollfree-restrictions>\n\nJoin from a video system or appl
 ication\nDial 24328466892@ig.webex.com<sip:24328466892@ig.webex.com>\nYou c
 an also dial 173.243.2.68 and enter your meeting number.\n\n\n\nIf you are 
 a host\, click here<https://ig.webex.com/webappng/sites/ig/meeting/info/b75
 f983e229543fc9608013ce8fd0a78> and login site to view host information.\n\n
 \nNeed help? Go to https://help.webex.com\n\n\n\nPlease ensure:\n\n  *   Yo
 ur meeting is up and ready to go 5-10 mins prior\n  *   Set up in a quiet r
 oom with a simple and presentable background\n  *   Dress professionally\n\
 nInterview Advice:\nKnow your resume – know what jobs you’ve worked at in y
 our past\, exactly what you did in each role\, and how long you were there.
  This helps you when answering a question about a specific position because
  you’ve already taken the time to review your experiences and clarify for y
 ourself exactly what your day-to-day responsibilities were\, and you don’t 
 spend time trying to remember in the interview.\n\nUse examples – this come
 s from knowing your resume. If you’re asked a question\, be able to relate 
 it to your experience.\nBe concise – being able to chat about your experien
 ce is very important but there’s also no reason to ramble. Once you’ve answ
 ered the question\, and used an example from your past experiences you can 
 confidently know that you’ve answered the question thoroughly. Remember to 
 speak slowly and clearly.\nBe prepared to answer the question\, “Tell me ab
 out yourself”. Please try to have an elevator pitch prepared - under 2 minu
 tes. Concise messaging and preparation for this question is key.\nPlease of
 fer small talk at the beginning and thank the interviewer for their time at
  the end.\n\nJob Description:\nClient: American Express\nTitle: Platform En
 gineer\nLocation: London: Belgrave House (76 Buckingham Palace Road\, Londo
 n SW1W 9AX)\nDuration: 12 months with extensions\n\nOverview of Day to Day:
 \nInsight Global is seeking multiple Platform Engineers to join a contract 
 opportunity for a leading financial services client. This team aims to buil
 d the tools and foundational technology that internal engineers can leverag
 e to build applications better - faster. The end goal is to integrate publi
 c cloud solutions into the organization in a safe\, compliant\, flexible\, 
 and user-friendly manner.\n\nWe are looking for a software engineer with at
  least 6 years of professional experience. The ideal candidate has led the 
 design and development of cloud-native applications written in Golang and h
 as extensive experience in DevOps\, including building CI/CD pipelines and 
 setting up cloud hosting environments. Engineers will also provide mentorsh
 ip to foster a culture of continuous learning and improvement. Additionally
 \, the candidates should excel in collaborating with cross-functional teams
  to ensure seamless integration and operation of cloud services.\n\nRequire
 ments:\n\n  *   Strong experience of platform engineering experience\n  *  
  Experience developing cloud-native applications in Golang\n  *   DevOps ex
 perience\; comfortable building CI/CD pipelines and setting up cloud hostin
 g environments\n  *   Deep familiarity with AWS and it's services and archi
 tecture\n  *   Tooling experience with Kubernetes and Docker\n  *   Experie
 nce with Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tools\n  *   Strong background in tes
 t-driven deployments and automation\n  *   Excellent communication and docu
 mentation skills\nPlusses:\n\n  *   Experience with ArgoCD\n  *   Experienc
 e with Terraform\n\nKindest regards\,\n\nEmily Bown\nConsultant Engagement 
 Lead | Professional Recruiter\nWomen’s Leadership Council | 2025\nInsight G
 lobal Ltd\nTel: +44 2045 206880\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/emily-bown/\nh
 ttps://www.insightglobal.co.uk/\n[A blue and black logo  Description automa
 tically generated]\n[A blue text on a black background  Description automat
