DESCRIPTION:Event Name\nJason - Axon Sync\n\nLocation: This is a Zoom web c
 onference.\n\nYou can join this meeting from your computer\, tablet\, or sm
 artphone.\nhttps://axon.zoom.us/j/99386543073\n\nOne tap mobile:\n+1 312 62
 6 6799\,\,99386543073#\n+1 646 558 8656\,\,99386543073#\n\nYou can also dia
 l in using your phone.\nUS: +1 312 626 6799\, +1 646 558 8656\, +1 646 931 
 3860\, +1 301 715 8592\, +1 305 224 1968\, +1 309 205 3325\, +1 669 444 917
 1\, +1 669 900 6833\, +16892781000\, +1 719 359 4580\, +1 253 205 0468\, +1
  253 215 8782\, +1 346 248 7799\, +1 360 209 5623\, +1 386 347 5053\, +1 50
 7 473 4847\, +1 564 217 2000\, +1 833 548 0282\, +1 833 928 4608\, +1 833 9
 28 4609\, +1 833 928 4610\, +1 877 853 5247\, +1 888 788 0099\, +1 833 548 
 0276\nMeeting ID: 993-865-43073\n\nJoin from a video system or application\
 nsip:99386543073@zoomcrc.com\nYou can also dial and enter your meeting ID 9
 93-865-43073\n\nPlease share anything that will help prepare for our meetin
 g.:\nHi Jason\n\nThis call is devoted to the Axon System Design Round Inter
 view Feedback (Tuesday\, 11 November⋅4:00 – 5:00pm) to me - Zufar Sunagatov
  - Senior Software Engineer.\n\nI have written to you email and you agreed 
 to have a call.\n\nMy email:\n""\nI hope you're doing well.\n\nI wanted to 
 follow up regarding the feedback call we discussed earlier. As you remember
 \, you kindly offered to speak with me after the interview\, but I unfortun
 ately became unwell and couldn’t join at that time. I really appreciate tha
 t you were open to helping\, and I would like to take you up on that offer 
 now.\n\nTo be clear — I’m not asking for written feedback.\nWhat I truly ne
 ed is a short 20–30 minute call with you.\n\nThe reason is simple:\nI genui
 nely want to understand where I did well and where I didn’t meet the bar. I
  have been doing many System Design interviews lately and usually perform s
 trongly\, so whenever I don’t pass\, I always try to identify my knowledge 
 gaps. It’s very important for me to understand them early and fix them prop
 erly.\n\nAnd since you were the person who conducted the System Design roun
 d\, your insight would be the most meaningful for me. You saw my reasoning 
 and decisions in real time — that kind of feedback simply cannot be replace
 d by a generic message.\n\nAlso\, I know from your background that you’re s
 omeone who genuinely cares about Software Engineering. You even moved from 
 management back into hands-on engineering\, which I respect a lot. People w
 ho make such decisions usually want to build great teams and help other eng
 ineers grow.\nThat’s why I’m reaching out to you directly — I believe your 
 guidance could help me improve in the right direction.\n\nIf you’re still o
 pen to a quick conversation\, could you please share a link where I can boo
 k a time with you for next week?\nI will adjust my schedule to whatever wor
 ks best on your side.\n\nThank you again for offering your help earlier — i
 t means a lot\, and I truly appreciate your willingness to support candidat
 es professionally.\n\nLooking forward to speaking with you.\n\n\nBest regar
 ds\,\nZufar Sunagatov\n""\n\nNeed to make changes to this event?\nCancel: h
 ttps://calendly.com/cancellations/5fe1c50c-e5a3-4e22-b303-d92a6910a70d\nRes
 chedule: https://calendly.com/reschedulings/5fe1c50c-e5a3-4e22-b303-d92a691
 0a70d\n\nPowered by Calendly https://calendly.com/\n
