DESCRIPTION:Join from a PC\, Mac\, iPad\, iPhone or Android device:\n    Pl
 ease click this URL to join. https://gradle.zoom.us/w/81568903878?tk=Un8XP3
 uUJ1VxRzd3rDjphJmIqjCV_K6rrSHWzh7Wbaw.DQcAAAAS_eKyxhZ2c0NyMGl4V1NiT19BSXpTW
 EU1VXNnAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA&uuid=WN_F8rxts3jTgSqyEYeDyws
 OQ\nDescription: Testing is a Good Thing\, right? Especially automated test
 ing. But the phrase "good things come to those who wait" doesn’t appeal to 
 a busy developer. When a test starts failing\, dropping everything to find 
 and fix the problem can be a frustrating experience.\nIn this webinar\, Tri
 sha Gee will cover several techniques for troubleshooting tests and go thro
 ugh some of the information you need to identify problems. She will also ra
 nt about flaky tests\, and how toxic they are to developer productivity. Th
 en she’ll share some tips on writing tests\, with an eye to making troubles
 hooting and debugging easier. Finally\, she’ll do a live coding demonstrati
 on and offer up some "best practices". Oh\, and AI & machine learning will 
 be mentioned at some point.\n\nDiscussion topics: \n- Why is it hard to tro
 ubleshoot tests?\n- What steps should you take to fix a test?\n- Why are fl
 aky tests toxic?\n- How can you write tests that are easier to fix?\n\nOr O
 ne tap mobile:\n    +13017158592\,\,81568903878# US (Washington DC)\n    +1
 3052241968\,\,81568903878# US\n\nOr join by phone:\n    Dial(for higher qua
 lity\, dial a number based on your current location):\n        US: +1 301 7
 15 8592  or +1 305 224 1968  or +1 309 205 3325  or +1 312 626 6799  or +1 
 646 876 9923  or +1 646 931 3860  or +1 253 205 0468  or +1 253 215 8782  o
 r +1 346 248 7799  or +1 360 209 5623  or +1 386 347 5053  or +1 507 473 48
 47  or +1 564 217 2000  or +1 669 444 9171  or +1 669 900 6833  or +1 689 2
 78 1000  or +1 719 359 4580 \n    Webinar ID: 815 6890 3878\n    Internatio
 nal numbers available: https://gradle.zoom.us/u/kexcL5B7b0\n\n
