DESCRIPTION:Eduard Tyantov has registered you to visit Meta. We look forwar
 d to welcoming you here at Meta! You will receive a visitor instruction ema
 il 24 hours before your arrival with more details about your visit. Remembe
 r to bring your photo ID with you to show the lobby receptionist after you 
 check in at the kiosk. If you have any other questions prior to your arriva
 l\, please reach out to your host.\nVisitor Privacy Statement\nI. Introduct
 ion\nThis Visitor Privacy Statement (“Statement”) informs you of how Meta P
 latforms Ireland Ltd. (collectively “we”/”our”/”us”/”MPIL”) collect and use
  information when you visit or are registered to visit our premises.\nII. W
 hat kinds of information do we collect and process?\nIf you are visiting on
 e of our premises or an employee registers you for a visit at our premises\
 , the types of information we collect include:\n\n  *\nYour name and email 
 address.\n  *\nThe Meta employee who hosts you.\n  *\nInformation about you
 r visit\, such as time and location.\n  *\nThe purpose of your visit (e.g. 
 whether you are making a social visit or a visit for business purposes).\n 
  *\nYour company if you are visiting as a vendor or for a business meeting.
 \n\nNote: Where video surveillance (“CCTV”) is in operation in our premises
 \, it is governed by our CCTV Privacy Statement.\nIII. Why do we use this i
 nformation?\nWe use this information:\n\n  *\nTo ensure the safety and secu
 rity of our assets and workforce.\n  *\nTo control access to our premises.\
 n  *\nTo ensure an efficient registration and check-in and check-out experi
 ence for visitors.\n\nIV. How do we work with vendors and service providers
 ?\nWe may work with third-party vendors and service providers to help us ad
 minister and improve our visitor management system. All third party vendors
  and service providers are required to have the necessary technical and org
 anizational security controls to appropriately safeguard and secure the dat
 a we share with them. Any visitor data shared with third parties is conside
 red confidential and must be stored securely according to Meta’s data secur
 ity guidelines.\nV. How do we respond to legal requests and prevent harm?\n
 We may be required to share your visitor information with regulators\, law 
 enforcement or other organisations in the following circumstances:\n\n  *\n
 When we have a good-faith belief it is necessary to: detect\, prevent and a
 ddress fraud\, unauthorized use of our systems or products\, violations of 
 our terms or policies\, or other harmful or illegal activity\; to protect o
 urselves (including our rights\, property or products)\, you or others\, in
 cluding as part of investigations or regulatory inquiries\; to prevent deat
 h or imminent bodily harm or should medical treatment be required.\n  *\nIn
  response to a legal request\, when the law requires us to do so. We can al
 so respond to legal requests when the response is required by law in that j
 urisdiction\, affects users or employees in that jurisdiction\, and is cons
 istent with internationally recognized standards.\n  *\nWhen we are under a
  legal obligation to do so\, we may provide your information to law enforce
 ment.\n\nInformation we receive about you might need to be retained for an 
 extended period if it is the subject of a legal request or obligation\, gov
 ernmental investigation\, or investigations of possible violations of our t
 erms or policies\, or otherwise necessary to prevent harm.\nWe may take the
 se actions pursuant to our legal obligations\, where necessary in our legit
 imate interests and the legitimate interests of others and where necessary 
 to protect the vital interest of individuals.\nVI. Data retention\nWe gener
 ally maintain the information described in Section II above for 2 years\, s
 tarting from your last visit\, unless legal obligations\, or our legitimate
  interests in ensuring the security of our assets\, workforce\, and others\
 , require us to retain the information for a longer period.\nWe retain info
 rmation (as set out in Section II above) only as long as required to comply
  with our legal obligations\, to resolve disputes and to enforce our contra
 ctual agreements\, or as necessary for our legitimate interests\, e.g. to e
 nsure the safety and security of our assets\, workforce\, and others.\nVII.
  What is our legal basis for processing data?\nOur legal basis for processi
 ng visitor personal data as detailed in this privacy statement is set out b
 elow:\n\n  *\nWith the consent of the visitor.\n  *\nAs necessary to comply
  with our legal obligations.\n  *\nWhen required to fulfill contractual obl
 igations.\n  *\nTo protect your vital interests\, or those of others.\n  *\
 nAs necessary for our (or others’) legitimate interests.\n\nVIII. How can y
 ou exercise your rights provided under the GDPR?\nUnder the General Data Pr
 otection Regulation (the 'GDPR')\, you have the following rights:\n\n  *\nR
 ight to access your information.\n  *\nRight to rectification.\n  *\nRight 
 to erasure (right to be forgotten).\n  *\nRight to data portability.\n  *\n
 Right to restriction of processing.\n  *\nRight to object.\n\nThis includes
  the right to object to\, and seek restriction of our processing of your da
 ta\, where we are pursuing our legitimate interests or those of a third par
 ty.\nTo exercise any of these rights\, please contact GlobalSecurityComplia
 nce@meta.com<mailto:GlobalSecurityCompliance@meta.com>.\nIX. How do we oper
 ate and transfer data as part of our global business?\nWe may share visitor
  information globally\, both internally within Meta\, and externally with o
 ur partners. Information we collect and process will be transferred or tran
 smitted to\, or stored and processed in the United States or other countrie
 s outside of where you live for the purposes as described in this Statement
 . These data transfers are necessary for our visitor management operations.
  We utilize standard contractual clauses<http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http
 %3A%2F%2Feur-lex.europa.eu%2Flegal-content%2FEN%2FTXT%2FPDF%2F%3Furi%3DCELE
 X%3A32010D0087&h=AT3VzmmdJgq173g6kNZ3LKUcLrNmzejQ_6ishhYTNghZGWpNTC75hfdFi0
 mIZyiioIKdjFhpVnJFX2UbTMD1SH44eBiU_6yf5vdVHc6td7vqDAeomHtGQUjWY9kuhJh2DwMrB
 yTn-SBoJifSwYeRKSHHvPyEGTOpzzTYdw> approved by the European Commission\, an
 d rely on the European Commission’s adequacy decisions<https://l.facebook.c
 om/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcommission.europa.eu%2Flaw%2Flaw-topic%2Fdata-prot
 ection%2Finternational-dimension-data-protection%2Fadequacy-decisions_en&h=
 AT0ogi0m--IlFWjl8x73thtSG8rDJRtD-eWcYPoN3FaY0BOtIZnwQe1IT344EMzQfjirGzjjiHu
 TiuOdwgAYEPsw6FEvtpkmiFnlJp-IrYJnU17v88txU9mN9ueGfYfdgCopcLm143DfLhxufwzUY-
 g1> about certain countries\, as applicable\, for data transfers from the E
 EA to the United States and other countries.\nX. How to contact Meta Platfo
 rms Ireland Ltd. with questions\nMeta Platforms Ireland Ltd. respectively\,
  are responsible for your information as independent data controllers\, and
  can be contacted by mail at:\nMeta Platforms Ireland Limited\n104 Serpenti
 ne Avenue\nBallsbridge\nDublin 4 Ireland\nYou also have the right to lodge 
 a complaint with your local supervisory authority.\nYou may also contact Gl
 obalSecurityCompliance@meta.com<mailto:GlobalSecurityCompliance@meta.com> w
 ith any questions.\nXI. How can you learn about changes to this Statement?\
 nWe may change this Statement from time to time.\n
